<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-30T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-30T20:00:00-05:00" n="293" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/537:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-30T20:00:00-05:00">November 30, 1929—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>399. You are directed immediately to transmit to the National Government
                            and to inform them that there is being communicated to the French
                            Government for transmission to the Soviet Government the following
                            statement:</p>
                        <p>[Here follows the text of the statement quoted in telegram 393, November
                            30, 8 p.m., to the Chargé in France, printed <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>